50|$|It is {{possible}} {{to get some of}} the benefits of a masonry oven without constructing a full oven. The most common method is the stoneware pizza stone, which stores heat while the oven is preheating and transmits it directly {{to the bottom of the}} pizza. Bread and meat can be cooked in a type of covered ceramic casserole dish known variously as a cloche, a Schlemmertopf (brand name), or the like. Most expensive is a ceramic or stoneware <b>oven</b> <b>liner</b> that provides many of the benefits of a cloche without restricting the baker to one size of pan.|$|E

